        <p>b26,300,000</p>
        <p>Share earns</p>
        <p>.18</p>
        <p>.34</p>
        <p>b-Included gains aggregating approximately $ 9.8 million pretax, or about 7 cents a share after-tax, from the sale by the company of stock of an equity affiliate. Income after preferred dividends in the latest first quarter was $ 10.2 million, or 18 cents a share, compared with $ 23.1 million, or 32 cents a share, in year-ago period. Sales are net sales. Mascotech said its first-quarter earnings were hurt by unspecified restructuring costs and results from certain operations it plans to divest. the company also said it had increased costs associated with its capital investment programs, launch costs for new products and increased steel costs.</p>
